gomodel:SYNGO_5191  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 2a-c: confocal imaging of immunofluorescence labeling for Eag1 (KCNH1) and PSD95 (DLG4) in cultured hippocampal neurons from rat brain showed partial co-localization (~65%).\n\nFigure 2d: biochemical fractions of rat brains showed Eag1 in synaptic fractions P2, synaptosomes, PSD1 and PSD2 (relative levels are; synaptosome = PSD1 > PSD2, whereas PSD95 is enriched SPM < PSD1 < PSD2. But note that Eag1 is known to also localize to the presynapse).\n\nFigure 3,5: overexpression of GFP-Eag1 constructs and mutant variants showed the A723-R807 segment of the protein sequence was required for postsynaptic localization.\n\nBased on the known transmembrane topology of this protein, \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was selected.. Experimental description: M&M: \"15-day pregnant Sprague-Dawley rats were purchased from the Facility for Animal Research of the National Yang-Ming University. Dissociated hippocampal cultures were prepared using a previously described protocol\"\n\nantibody:\nrabbit anti-rEag1 described and validated at PMID:15706225" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5191" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

